dian safety manuals and training, including night-time travel, safety in public places, safety of strangers, etc.<\/li>\n<li>Multi-national mixed language courses in the morning<\/li>\n<li>Afternoon Western etiquette training, including dining, snacks and coffee experiences (Starbucks, Tim Horton, Subway, A&amp;W), Western Stone etiquette (Milestone), Interpersonal Basics, etc. (SSC-Canada staff actually bring students to the experience, students do not bear the cost)<\/li>\n<li>A one-day tour of Vancouver on Saturday includes: City bus to explore more than 20 Vancouver Downtown attractions including: Glenview Island, English Bay, Stanley Park Chinatown, Gastown, Five Sails Square, Vancouver Arts Hall, Vancouver Aquarium, etc.<\/li>\n<li>Survival English common language manuals, including idioms and manuals for food, clothing, housing, living, medical, etc.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Textbooks published by SSC-Canada provided to students:<\/p>\n<p>British Education System Explained<\/p>\n<p>Canada Safety Training Manual<\/p>\n<p>Survival English Common Phrases<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-4 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-5 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\"><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;width:100%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\