ervice throughout the year)<\/p>\n<p><strong>Services Provided<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>Landing on the first day<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Pick-up at Vancouver Airport for homestay<\/li>\n<li>Call to parents to confirm arrival<\/li>\n<li>Support and counseling about schools and accommodations, including shopping, restaurants, transportation, clinics, banks, libraries, etc.<\/li>\n<li>Handle \u201cfive cards\u201d for students: phone cards, bank cards, transportation cards, medical insurance cards, and common contact cards (this service is exclusively provided by SSC-Canada).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Important Documents Support<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Update passports, Canadian visas, and student visas (surcharges, embassy fees, etc.)<\/p>\n<p><strong>School Learning Support<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Help students complete the registration test at the Education Bureau and testing center<\/li>\n<li>Help students prepare school materials<\/li>\n<li>One attendance at a parent meeting per semester<\/li>\n<li>Two official emergency contacts for the school (Note: The additional contact is different from the guardian)<\/li>\n<li>Keeping updated guardian contact information in the school office<\/li>\n<li>Signing documents for students who need to have a legal guardian for their school<\/li>\n<li>Provide proof of student absence (absence, late arrival, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>Provide required consent based on academic programs and activities<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-7 fusion_builder_column_1_2 1_2 fusion-one-half fusion-column-last\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;width:50%;width:calc(50% - ( ( 4% ) * 0.5 ) );\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\"><div class=\"fusion-column-content-centered\"><div class=\"fusion-column-content\"><div class=\"fusion-image-element fusion-image-align-center in-legacy-container\" styl