rapper-legacy\"><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;width:100%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:#dcdcdc;border-color:#dcdcdc;border-top-width:1px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-7 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling fusion-equal-height-columns\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-padding-top:5%;--awb-padding-bottom:5%;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-9 fusion_builder_column_1_2 1_2 fusion-one-half fusion-column-first\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;width:50%;width:calc(50% - ( ( 4% ) * 0.5 ) );margin-right: 4%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\"><div class=\"fusion-column-content-centered\"><div class=\"fusion-column-content\"><div class=\"fusion-image-element fusion-image-align-center in-legacy-container\" style=\"text-align:center;--awb-caption-title-font-family:var(--h2_typography-font-family);--awb-caption-title-font-weight:var(--h2_typography-font-weight);--awb-caption-title-font-style:var(--h2_typography-font-style);--awb-caption-title-size:var(--h2_typography-font-size);--awb-caption-title-transform:var(--h2_typography-text-transform);--awb-caption-title-line-height:var(--h2_typography-line-height);--awb-caption-title-letter-spacing:var(--h2_typography-letter-spacing);\"><div class=\"imageframe-align-center\"><span class=\" fusion-imageframe imageframe-none imageframe-4 hover-type-none\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" title=\"seabird-768584_960_720\" src=\"http:\/\/site-ssccanada-live-1523224571-vytetvzxegbutqs7mm9.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/seabird-768584_960_720.jpg\" alt class=\"img-responsive wp-image-84\" srcset=\"http:\/\/site-ssccanada-live-1523224571-vytetvzxegbutqs7mm9.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/seabird-768584_960_720-200x300.jpg 200w, http:\/\/site-ssccanada-live-1523224571-vytetvzxegbutqs7mm9.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/seabird-768584_960_720-400x600.jpg 400w, http:\/\/site-ssccanada-live-1523224571-vytetvzxegbutqs7mm9.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/seabird-768584_960_720.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/span><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-10 fusion_builder_column_1_2 1_2 fusion-one-half fusion-column-last\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;width:50%;width:calc(50% - ( ( 4% ) * 0.5 ) );\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\"><div class=\"fusion-column-content-centered\"><div class=\"fusion-column-content\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-5\"><p><span style=\"color: #7b197a; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>IV &#8211; Five-year Guardian Service<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><strong>Service Introduction\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>The\u00a0comprehensive guardianship service for 5 years\u00a0includes guardian legal letters for use of visas, including the placement of homestay families, responsibility for the first day of landing in Vancouver, the first day of the Education Bureau\/school placement; supervision of important documents; school communication, Including participation, solving homework, living and other aspects such as studying, living, and entertainment.\u00a0Its role is: the role of the liaison person and the solver, including personally participating in problem solving, such as the student&#8217;s conflict with the host family, the service assisting in finding homestay families, and assisting with moving services.<\/p>\n<h2>Service Content<\/h2>\n<p><strong><u>Landing on the first day<\/u><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Pick-up at Vancouver Airport for homestay<\/li>\n<li>Call parents for peace<\/li>\n<li>Field guidance around the school and accommodation, including shopping, food, transportation, clinic hospitals, banks, libraries, etc.<\/li>\n<li>Handle \u201cfive cards\u201d for students: phone cards, bank cards, transportation cards, medical insurance cards, and common contact cards (exclusively provided by Canadian supervised care company SSC-Canada).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong><u>Important documents assist in supervision<\/u><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Update passports, Canadian visas, and student visas (surcharges, embassy fees, etc.)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong><u>Communication with school<\/u><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Help students complete the test of registration at the Education Bureau and registration and testing center<\/li>\n<li>Schedule an appointment with a course consultant for students<\/li>\n<li>Help students prepare materials for school registration<\/li>\n<li>Anything about the student serves as an official school contact<\/li>\n<li>Keep correct guardian contact information in school office<\/li>\n<li>Sign documents for students who need to sign a legal guardian for the school<\/li>\n<li>Provide additional contacts for emergencies (additional contacts are different from guardians)<\/li>\n<li>Provide proof of student absence (absence, late arrival, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>Provide required consent based on academic programs and activities<\/li>\n<li>Attend Parent Teacher Meeting<\/li>\n<li>Regularly communicate with the school on school-related issues (including student attendance and performance at school, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>Provide students current school student visas\/permits to education bureaus<\/li>\n<li>Every two months to the school to understand the situation of students, to report to parents about student learning<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong><u>Communicating with parents<\/u><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Regularly communicate with school and parents about school matters<\/li>\n<li>When the student has any academic, attendance, behavior, emotional issues, notify the parents in time<\/li>\n<li>At the end of the semester, the transcripts will be handed over to the parents. In addition, similar or related documents with transcripts will be handed over to the parents during the semester, such as the mid-term Report Cards, the usual attendance records, and the student\u2019s feedback on normal performance.<\/li>\n<li>The student provides the student himself with all the relevant information in case of a major accident, and Party B immediately informs the parents by telephone and provides assistance.\u00a0(For example, the student was infringed by a major personal injury, the student suffered a major illness, and the student, unknowingly, participated in some affairs that violated Canadian local laws, etc.)<\/li>\n<li>Students provide information on the need for the school to hold a parent meeting, and Party B attends on time.\u00a0(Some parents&#8217; conferences or meetings where the school asks guardians to attend are not mandatory; if it is only a general briefing, the guardian will contact the school board to decide whether to participate in the meeting or explain the advice to the students in advance.)<\/li>\n<li>And any other matters that must be handled by a legal guardian in accordance with Canadian law.\u00a0(such as accessing student&#8217;s school records)<\/li>\n<li>Timely and regularly send school communication reports to parents (every 2 months)<\/li>\n<li>Send the student\u2019s schedule and transcripts to parents before each semester<\/li>\n<li>Promptly communicate with parents and tell parents and children about their study and life<\/li>\n<li>Promptly notify parents of students&#8217; travel plans and obtain parental consent<\/li>\n<li>Assist parents to visit students in Canada and send them to China<\/li>\n<li>Learn that the student is ill and admitted to hospital, rush to the hospital as soon as possible, and call the parents<\/li>\n<li>Ordering and delivering birthday gifts on behalf of parents<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-8 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-11 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\"><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;width:100%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:#dcdcdc;border-color:#dcdcdc;border-top-width:1px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-9 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling fusion-equal-height-columns\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-padding-top:5%;--awb-padding-bottom:5%;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-12 fusion_builder_column_1_2 1_2 fusion-one-half fusion-column-first\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;widt