span><\/h3>\n<p>If you are considered a minor in Canada, defined as under the age of 18 (19 in British Columbia and New Brunswick), you will require a custodian in order to obtain your study permit from Citizenship and Immigration Canada (CIC).<\/p>\n<p>If you are seen as a minor in Canada and you are not accompanied by a legal Guardian studying in Canada, then you will need to have a guardian, Custodian, to issue a student visa. This guardian must be Canadian nationals or residents with permanent residence.\u00a0Even if you do not need a study visa (time is less than 6 months), according to SSC-Canada&#8217;s requirements, all minors, as long as they are not accompanied by their parents and are studying or traveling in Canada alone, they must accept the service of SSC-Canada. Both students with and without a study permit visa need a local guardian (Custodian).<\/p>\n<p>For related information please see Citizenship &amp; Immigration Canada&#8217;s\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.cic.gc.ca\/EnGLish\/study\/study-minors.asp\">\u201cStudying in Canada \u2013 Minors\u201d<\/a><\/p>\n<p><em>Please\u00a0<\/em><em>note that students\u00a0<\/em><em>care\u00a0<\/em><em>who\u00a0<\/em><em>custodians\u00a0<\/em><em>is different from the method\u00a0<\/em><em>given guardianship\u00a0<\/em><em>of people parents\u00a0<\/em><em>guardians.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-12 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling fusion-equal-height-columns\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-17 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\"><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;width:100%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;border-color:#e0dede;border-top-width:1px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-13 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling fusion-equal-height-columns\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-18 fusion_builder_column_1_2 1_2 fusion-one-half fusion-column-first\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;width:50%;width:calc(50% - ( ( 4% ) * 0.5 ) );margin-right: 4%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-8\"><h3><span style=\"color: #7b197a;\">Required Statutory Notarization Letters for Studying Visas:<\/span><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The first notarized document must be signed by the parents or legal guardians of the minor child in the child&#8217;s country of origin. Legal Notarization Letter Authorized by a Parent or Legal Guardian Visa<\/li>\n<li>The second notarized document must be signed by the custodian in Canada. Legal Notarization Letter Signed by the Acting Guardian in Canada<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong><u>Canada\u00a0<\/u><\/strong><strong><u>&#8216;s definition\u00a0<\/u><\/strong><strong><u>of\u00a0<\/u><\/strong><strong><u>minors<\/u><\/strong><\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"221\"><strong>Province\/Territory<\/strong><\/td>\n<td wi